results.name: a(n) = n divided by its characteristic cube divisor A056191.
comment: Different from A056552: e.g. a(16) = 16, while A056552(16) = 2.
link: Amiram Eldar, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
formula: Multiplicative with a(p^e)=p^e for even e, a(p)=p, a(p^e)=p^(e-3) for odd e>1. - _Vladeta Jovovic_, Apr 30 2002
mathematica: f[p_, e_] := If[EvenQ[e], p^e, If[e == 1, p, p^(e - 3)]]; a[n_] := Times @@ f @@@ FactorInteger[n]; Array[a, 100] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Sep 06 2020 *)
